<paragraph blockId="7.[189,1398,682,782]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Although Cockerell labeled the 
<typeStatus box="[557,608,682,708]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">type</typeStatus>
specimen as a new species, it was published as a variety of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lepeletier" authorityYear="1841" box="[1289,1391,682,708]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitens">
<emphasis box="[1289,1391,682,708]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">C. nitens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This species is only known from male specimens and could actually correspond to a metander male of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lepeletier" authorityYear="1841" box="[189,293,756,782]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitens">
<emphasis box="[189,293,756,782]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">C. nitens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
